==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harmonometer
<hw>Har`mo*nom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(-n⟦ocr⟧m"⟦esl⟧*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"armoni`a</grk> harmony + <ets>meter</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>harmonometre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring
the harmonic relations of sounds. It is often a monochord furnished with
movable bridges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmony</ent>⟦br⟧
